blue: 96%

red: 40%
you will usually lose money no matter what color you pick but yellow and red dont pay out anywhere near enough to be worth the chance they get rolled
The formula is the amount of squares, divided by the total number of squares in the board, multiplied by the payout
blue: 12√∑25/2=.96
green: 8√∑25/3=.96
yellow: 4√∑25/5=.8
red: 1√∑25/10=.4
